>> >How would one write a program to crack an rsa encrypted message.
>> >If you have the public key and the cypher text, what would be the procedure.
>> Factor the public key, create the private key and decrypt. 

                                           e
An other way: Given a chypher text    y = m   mod n    of a message m:

Compute the e-th root modulo n of y (the so-called "RSA-root"). This 
MIGHT be simpler than factoring n (no one knows).

